Gupta comes with cross-functional experience of 19 years in spearheading marketing and sales operations across various industries and is an experienced marketer with expertise in handling senior level assignments in both the product and services environment.<img src="http://c.biz-file.com/c/1804/436530-625x325.jpg?2" alt="Rajesh Gupta" width="625" height="325">Rajesh GuptaA post graduate in business management specialising in marketing, Gupta started his career with Monsanto India in 1999 and moved to Piaggio in 2007 as their head of marketing. His last position with M&M was that of senior general manager: commercial vehicle sales, rural sales and brand activation. <img src="http://c.biz-file.com/c/1711/420172-120x120.jpg?2" alt="Photo: Car Magazine" width="120" height="120">Bakkie takes luxurious personaMahindra SA has had some rather cheap yet crude products, mainly aimed at farmers and those in the mining sector...By Lerato Matebese 24 Nov 2017He reportedly joins Mahindra South Africa at a critical juncture. With its introduction of several new products in the passenger segment and the recent launch of its “Mahindra Pikup”, M&M has been experiencing excellent volume growth defying industry trends. “Taking a lead from our core philosophy of 'rise', we would be working on our strategy to position Mahindra as a 'most passionate company' in SA. We have a desire to lead this transformation across all our touchpoints of sales and service. We know that our right to win will revolve around our abilities to pursue every single additional sales by offering delight to our customers,” says Gupta.